SIMPLE: mithridate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mithridate
<hw>Mith"ri*date</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An antidote against poison, or a composition in form of an
electuary, supposed to serve either as a remedy or a preservative
against poison; an alexipharmic; -- so called from <person>King
<etsep>Mithridates</etsep></person>, its reputed inventor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Love is] a drop of the true elixir; no <qex>mithridate</qex> so
effectual against the infection of vice.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 933 --></p>

<p><ent>Mithridatic</ent>⟦br⟧
